snippet.textDisplay:
There's a message to this, choose your role models carefully.

You may not be surrounded by the right upbringing, may not have a mother or father to look up to. Or, maybe you do, but they just aren't able to give you the support that you need. Set your sights high, look for a fine example of where you'd like to take your life, mentally mark that spot. The universal GPS (or UPS? Universal Positioning system) will walk you through the path to your destination. It's time to stop playing a victim of our setbacks in life, the best we can do is try. If you don't, you'll definitely do worse than attempting. If it gets tough enough then cry. Cry, cry, cry. First the tears then cry your story out to all sorts of people, don't be defeated in silence. Someone is bound to hear your cry and either help out or set you in a direction that will help and allow you to live another day or two. Or a month. Or a year. Or maybe, it'll set you free and lift the barrier blocking the path to your dream course, job, career or whatever it is you're desiring. Choose your idols wisely kids.

Awesome tribute to an idol. My idol when I was a teen. That served it's purpose, now I have other idols serving their purpose for my current journey.

Stay positive.
